title: Nuclear level structures in 160,162Tb studied with 161,163Dy(t,alpha) reactions

x4freetext: Nuclear level structures in 160,162Tb studied with
161,163Dy(t,alpha) reactions

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.794, p.149 (2007)

x4freetext: Enriched Dy samples, enrichment to 90.41% for 161Dy and
96.85% for 163Dy. Thicknesses of the samples ranged
from 50microg/cm2 to 80microg/cm2
Reaction products were analysed with the
Enge split-pole magnetic spectrograph, equipped at the
focal plane with  position-sensitive Si detectors .
Spectra were recorded also with Ilford K-minus-
photographic plates, which were used for determination
of excitation energies
